<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>REST on Scott Obert</title><link>https://scottobert.com/tags/rest/</link><description>Recent content in REST on Scott Obert</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><copyright>&amp;copy;2022 Scott Obert</copyright><lastBuildDate>Sun, 26 Sep 2021 11:00:00 -0700</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://scottobert.com/tags/rest/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>API Design Patterns for Modern Applications</title><link>https://scottobert.com/posts/api-design-patterns-modern-applications/</link><pubDate>Sun, 26 Sep 2021 11:00:00 -0700</pubDate><guid>https://scottobert.com/posts/api-design-patterns-modern-applications/</guid><description>&lt;p>Modern API design has evolved far beyond simple CRUD operations. Today&amp;rsquo;s applications require APIs that are resilient, scalable, and developer-friendly while supporting diverse client needs and complex business workflows. This guide explores proven patterns that address these challenges.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="foundational-design-principles">Foundational Design Principles&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="api-first-development">API-First Development&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>Design your API before implementation to ensure consistency and usability:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-typescript" data-lang="typescript">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#75715e">// Define API contract first
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#75715e">&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef">interface&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">UserAPI&lt;/span> {
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#75715e">// Resource operations
